Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.97,0:00:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.85,0:00:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hopefully, we can hush everything up...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.31,0:00:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure could use a drink right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got some whiskey bonbons!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.28,0:00:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.20,0:00:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got these from a very hot chick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.66,0:00:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.12,0:00:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look depressed...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.42,0:00:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't trust anyone now...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.71,0:00:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell me, if you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.97,0:00:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.55,0:00:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought that Inspector Zeman, of all\Npeople, would do something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.35,0:00:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believed in him, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.19,0:01:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.86,0:01:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only peace in my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.91,0:01:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An unbelievable, shocking development has\Noccurred at the Prague police department.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.51,0:02:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Chief Hamrik, Head Detective Patera, and Detective\NJanacek were all found dead by poisoning.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.23,0:03:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What could have forced the killer to carry\Nout such a bold and horrific act?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.19,0:03:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the shady connection rumored to exist\Nbetween the police and the secret police...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.15,0:03:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will this event trigger the discovery\Nof an even greater scandal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.66,0:03:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who the killer is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've heard that the substance used in the murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.79,0:03:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a muscle relaxant. Any comments?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.79,0:03:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true that even the late Chief Hamrik\Nhad ties to the secret police?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.38,0:03:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Well... that's, uh...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.38,0:03:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Any connections to last week's\Nmurder of Inspector Zeman?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.89,0:03:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}W-We're still... investigating that matter...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.27,0:03:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're saying that the investigators believe\Nthat all these cases are somehow related?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.40,0:03:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.57,0:03:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What I'm trying to say is that we're going\Nto explore every aspect of these cases...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.03,0:03:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm terribly sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's in charge of another case, so...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say anything unnecessary! Hurry up and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.95,0:03:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When will you be holding an official press conference?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.96,0:04:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We will hold a press conference once\Nwe have some information.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So please wait patiently until then.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.25,0:04:07.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That'll take too long!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.58,0:04:26.71,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,113)\pos(356,360)}The Two Darknesses
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.84,0:04:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.82,0:04:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More questioning?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.24,0:04:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.24,0:04:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was ordered by my superiors to re-examine\Nthis case from the very beginning, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.66,0:04:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already talked to the children who were\Ntaken in by other orphanages, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to put yourself in these children's shoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.00,0:04:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These children...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They saw Mr. Petrov, a man who raised\Nthem in place of their parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.84,0:04:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and his assistant die right before their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.05,0:04:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, there are children who have nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.93,0:05:01.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like them to forget all about it\Nas soon as possible, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.68,0:05:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.10,0:05:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it's not something they'll ever forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.31,0:05:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, someone they loved was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.24,0:05:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifteen minutes per child!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask them anything too graphic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, living there was fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.04,0:05:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both Mr. Petrov and Ms. Ana were really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.92,0:05:34.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, I want to ask you some things\Nabout the day of the incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the guy who visited that dayr Mr.\NGrimmer, ever come by before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that was his first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.72,0:05:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think he was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.52,0:05:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were Mr. Petrov and Mr. Grimmer\Nfriendly with each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.02,0:05:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't seem to be all that friendly, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.03,0:05:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were talking about something really complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:06:00.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys know a little German, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.37,0:06:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kinds of things were they talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.08,0:06:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something about, "This place is unauthorized..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, "I'll tell the police. "
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.29,0:06:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.30,0:06:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, something about "education" and "experiments."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Experiments?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.26,0:06:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.35,0:06:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.31,0:06:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay if it's something you don't\Nwant to remember, Honza.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.02,0:06:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and something about "Kinderheim 511."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.85,0:06:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinderheim... 511...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.40,0:06:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what that place is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.07,0:06:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no such orphanage in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.66,0:06:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Mr. Grimmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.08,0:06:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a really nice man!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.42,0:06:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Izzy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.84,0:06:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We played soccer together!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.80,0:06:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't really good at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.34,0:07:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Mr. Grimmer looked like he was having fun, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was really bad at heading the ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.43,0:07:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even landed on his butt!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.18,0:07:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably the second worst, next to Honza!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and also...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.23,0:07:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you were the leader\Nat that orphanage, Antonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.69,0:07:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't like I was the leader or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.74,0:07:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just because I was a little older than everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.03,0:07:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honza and Izzy said they were questioned\Nabout Mr. Grimmer, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.13,0:07:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.88,0:07:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.13,0:07:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.59,0:07:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that you suspect Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.47,0:07:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer isn't the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.10,0:07:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was playing soccer with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.39,0:07:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when we came back, Mr. Petrov\Nand Ms. Ana had already been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told this to the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.69,0:07:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.19,0:08:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw a pretty blonde lady leave\Nour house and walk away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to arrest him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.75,0:08:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrest who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.33,0:08:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't decided anything like that yet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.55,0:08:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to meet up with him soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.06,0:08:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We made a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.60,0:08:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already decided where we'll meet, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.81,0:08:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.19,0:08:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may end up arresting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.90,0:08:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he would never kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.17,0:08:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.09,0:09:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.05,0:09:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone doing okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.55,0:09:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're totally fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you guys weren't crying like babies?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.97,0:09:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy wet his bed twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to wet my bed until I was\Nmuch older than you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.73,0:09:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Antonin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still have that thing I left with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.66,0:09:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for taking good care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is something important that your grandpa gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.84,0:09:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.71,0:09:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.76,0:09:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, take care of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.34,0:09:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play soccer, Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.01,0:09:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.10,0:09:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't have the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.56,0:09:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me introduce you to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.22,0:09:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're our new friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.77,0:09:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.06,0:09:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll play for a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.57,0:10:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.53,0:10:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Now's your chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.78,0:10:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pass me the ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.45,0:10:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They got the ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.96,0:10:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a weak dribble!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.42,0:10:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, defender! Get a grip, will you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.23,0:10:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.27,0:10:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.70,0:10:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Mr. Grimmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.74,0:10:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you come to arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.83,0:10:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in front of the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.29,0:11:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare wave a gun around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.00,0:11:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same goes for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss me your gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.71,0:11:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You threw it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.63,0:11:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never carried one with me before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.81,0:11:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it you who killed Inspector Zeman?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.81,0:11:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.94,0:11:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.15,0:11:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was half dead after being tortured...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.07,0:11:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your nails...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.62,0:11:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not the one who fired the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.62,0:11:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although... I may have killed the other two...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Grimmer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.79,0:11:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you taking a break for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.13,0:11:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My team's short one player now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.55,0:11:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.84,0:11:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:12:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who told the children to\Ninvite you to play soccer with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching you all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.11,0:12:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.11,0:12:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.28,0:12:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.03,0:12:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During these past few days...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.66,0:12:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been betrayed by so many people...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.37,0:12:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand anything anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.37,0:12:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to believe in...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.04,0:12:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one you can believe in is yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.21,0:12:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you're the only one you can believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.13,0:12:30.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you promise that you won't run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.10,0:12:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you staying right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.47,0:12:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Pavla Hotel, Room 302.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.64,0:12:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come by whenever you're sure that I'm the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.20,0:12:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll entrust that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.41,0:12:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's the cause of this chain of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.79,0:13:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a key to a safety deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This storefront signboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's very old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear it was for a tavern that was\Nhere two hundred years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.05,0:13:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though the tavern's no longer\Nhere, the sign still hangs there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.18,0:13:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though the color has faded...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it has become a landmark of this street.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.35,0:13:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must have been wars and chaos...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.65,0:13:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it has managed to remain standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.52,0:13:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even during the fire around ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.36,0:13:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.53,0:13:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman moved into the second floor with her child.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.28,0:13:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a beautiful woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.16,0:13:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she seemed kind of gloomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.41,0:13:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She almost never went outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.50,0:13:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I heard she was using a false name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then one day, a black car suddenly came...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:13:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and took both the mother and her child away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.34,0:14:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We used to gossip about whether she was linked\Nto the anti-government movement or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.18,0:14:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, talk like that was common.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the reign of terror during\Nthe final years of communism...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.23,0:14:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those were terrible times...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.36,0:14:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't uncommon for someone to suddenly disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't that woman have twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.45,0:14:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she only had one child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That child had a really pretty face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:32.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it a boy or a girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.12,0:14:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.37,0:14:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, I wonder which it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When children are young, there are times\Nwhen you can't really tell, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.76,0:14:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, aside from the mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.93,0:14:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone was saying how awful it was that\Nthey even took away an innocent little child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the fire started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.64,0:14:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone thought the fire started in a vacant room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:14:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but surprisingly, that child was still in the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.65,0:15:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The child was probably released, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.03,0:15:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it got lonely and hungry and\Nset a fire to make something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.28,0:15:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the child?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.45,0:15:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember correctly, it went missing\Nright after being rescued from the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what happened to the child after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.71,0:15:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if that child was one of the twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.76,0:15:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if one of the twins was taken away...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.59,0:15:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while the other stayed behind in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.13,0:15:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That's a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.60,0:15:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you so obsessed with this twin thing, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.69,0:15:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That tall man named Grimmer you\Nsaid I should investigate...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.57,0:15:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he's the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.66,0:15:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.04,0:15:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Mr. Suk, for an amateur like\Nme telling you such useless things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.21,0:15:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.25,0:16:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned a lot of things while chasing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.55,0:16:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I was all worked up, thinking\NI would avenge Inspector Zeman...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.35,0:16:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But as I investigated...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.06,0:16:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found out that even Inspector Zeman,\N\Nsomeone I once admired...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.89,0:16:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was actually really corrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the chief of police and my two senior\Ndetectives were poisoned to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.90,0:16:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After hearing about the poisonings...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.16,0:16:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was left completely speechless...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.91,0:16:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought to myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.45,0:16:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just how far the realm of darkness\Nhas spread in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darkness...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.96,0:16:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Czechoslovakian secret police that\Nthey say are behind this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.80,0:16:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're an organization controlled by the\Nformer Ministry of Domestic Affairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.09,0:16:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they worked for the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.34,0:16:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But during the democratic revolution\Nthat occurred about ten years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.84,0:16:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the organization was dissolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.93,0:16:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although the officials were tried in court...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.97,0:16:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,several of them escaped to the underground...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.14,0:17:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are still scheming to regain\Nthe power they once had.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.31,0:17:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That much I do know!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why must there be so many victims?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.07,0:17:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are the former secret police really\Nthe only ones behind all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How far has the darkness spread\Ninto the world we now live in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.16,0:17:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe in anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.67,0:17:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mr. Grimmer told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.42,0:17:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that in the end, I'm the only one I can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.17,0:17:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that said, he entrusted something to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.64,0:17:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.60,0:17:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for going on about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.39,0:17:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.31,0:17:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't know your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.56,0:17:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! It's fine! You don't have to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.15,0:17:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.45,0:17:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought trust could only be achieved if people\Nknew each other's names and backgrounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can tell you anything like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.42,0:18:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My parents were both teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.13,0:18:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my father got marked by the authorities for being\Ninvolved in the pro-democracy movement...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.01,0:18:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my mother left my father,\Nthinking only of my future.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.39,0:18:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I said I wanted to become a detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.94,0:18:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my mother protested vehemently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.94,0:18:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you want to become a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.65,0:18:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My friends mentioned it before at the bar, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.41,0:18:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you were actually influenced\Nby those detective dramas...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.12,0:18:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.99,0:18:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been my dream since I was a child
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.29,0:18:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was always acting out scenes from those things
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't laugh so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.88,0:18:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.36,0:19:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sor what was the thing you were entrusted with?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.03,0:19:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said a while back that you got something\Nfrom that Grimmer person.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.86,0:19:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A key to a bank's safety deposit box.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.37,0:19:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A safety deposit box?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.95,0:19:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's supposed to be something\Nreally important locked inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.33,0:19:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You remember the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.21,0:19:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where a German named Petrov who was operating\Nan unlicensed orphanage was murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.84,0:19:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.05,0:19:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the safety deposit box...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.59,0:19:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's supposed to be data from Petrov's\Nhuman experiments or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.76,0:19:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that this chain of events is all due to that, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.43,0:19:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.68,0:19:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't tell the police or anyone else about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.69,0:19:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this isn't something I can solve by myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.48,0:19:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why your mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.99,0:19:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why your mother opposed your becoming a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.16,0:20:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She thought about what could happen to your and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.33,0:20:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sense something very dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you must not tell anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.17,0:20:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same way your mother did, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.98,0:20:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.02,0:20:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.11,0:20:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.78,0:20:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a nice name...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.45,0:20:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're German?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.95,0:20:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.75,0:20:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.53,0:21:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening, Mr. Tulunka.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.91,0:21:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what a nice evening it is, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.45,0:21:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good evening, Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.58,0:21:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening, Ms. Jalka.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.51,0:22:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A key to a safety deposit box, huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.11,0:22:31.28,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.28,0:22:44.71,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.28,0:22:44.71,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.71,0:22:47.67,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.67,0:23:01.35,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.67,0:23:01.35,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.95,0:23:26.21,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.21,0:23:34.63,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:37.09,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
